Adam Ashley-Cooper is the oldest player ever selected by the @wallabies  for a World Cup. With three tries in Super Rugby 2019 for the @nswwaratahs, we look forward to seeing that vintage dive in Japan!⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RWC2019

Ben Smith enters his second World Cup as the oldest @allblacks on the list. With runs like this one we expect to see plenty more of him turning the youngsters inside out.⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RWC2019

We can’t wait to see what All Blacks’ playmaker Richie Mo’unga brings to his first World Cup! We can only imagine it’ll be more of this.⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣#RWC2019

WORLD CUP FOCUS | Nicolas Sanchez, Los Pumas⁣
⁣⁣
⁣Nicolas Sanchez sits third in the all-time Argentina World Cup points list. He looks certain to add to his 97 points from seven matches as he suits up for his third RWC appearance.⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RWC2019

WORLD CUP FOCUS | Marika Koroibete, Wallabies⁣
⁣⁣
⁣Who’s pumped to see Rebel Marika Koroibete bouncing around at the 2019 World Cup in a few weeks?⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RWC2019

PLAYER OF THE WEEK | 2019 International Tests⁣
⁣⁣
⁣@allblacks’ Ardie Savea was everywhere in their shutout of the Wallabies. Showing his brute strength with two early runs that set the tone for his team. His tackling and scrum work was instrumental and a late steal put the icing on the cake of their big win.⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#PlayeroftheWeek #NZLvAUS

PLAY OF THE WEEK | 2019 International Tests⁣
⁣⁣
⁣Could we have expected anything less from Sevu Reece’s first try in the @allblacks jersey? His sensational toe-poke, balance and pure speed showing his sheer class. We expect to see more at the World Cup!⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#PlayoftheWeek #NZLvAUS

TRY OF THE WEEK | 2019 International Tests⁣
⁣⁣
⁣Springbok’s S’busiso Nkosi scored two phenomenal individual tries in their final home test before the World Cup. His second is our pick as he spun and sidestepped around three defenders to score their second try in the win.⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#TryoftheWeek #RSAvARG

DEBUTANT | Liam Wright, Australia⁣
⁣⁣
⁣Reds’ flanker Liam Wright looks set to make his Wallabies’ debut tonight after impressing in Super Rugby. Can he be the spark off the bench to help them clinch their first Bledisloe Cup in 16 years?⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#SuperRugby #BledisloeCup #NZLvAUS

TRC MOST TRIES 2019 | Herschel Jantjies⁣
⁣⁣
⁣What an introduction to International rugby @bokrugby Herschel Jantjies had, finishing with three tries in the shortened series. His equaliser against the All Blacks will be remembered for a long time!⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RugbyChampionship #TRC2019

TRC MOST TRIES 2019 | Reece Hodge⁣
⁣⁣
⁣With the conclusion of the Rugby Championship, let’s look at the top try scorers in the shortened 2019 series. @wallabies Reece Hodge scored an equal high of three tries, including a double in their big win over the @allblacks.⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RugbyChampionship #TRC2019

PLAYER OF THE WEEK | 2019 Rugby Championship Rd 3⁣
⁣⁣
⁣@bokrugby’s Handre Pollard topped the individual points list for the 2019 Rugby Championship with 42. He scored a South African record of 31 points against @lospumasuar, including two sensational tries, to pick up his second Player of the Week in a row!⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RugbyChampionship #TRC2019 #PlayeroftheWeek #ARGvRSA

PLAY OF THE WEEK | 2019 Rugby Championship Rd 3⁣
⁣⁣
⁣With his 78th minute try, Kurtley Beale helped the @wallabies post the largest ever score against an All Blacks side in their 47-26 victory. His 19th international try could be the sweetest!⁣
⁣⁣
⁣#RugbyChampionship #TRC2019 #PlayoftheWeek #AUSvNZL
